WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:26.736 --> 00:00:30.156
Hey. yo. Reggie! Re-up.

3
00:00:56.223 --> 00:00:58.768
I thought you were too sick to practice.

4
00:00:58.851 --> 00:01:01.395
Done with all that. Coach.

5
00:01:03.189 --> 00:01:05.107
When's the last time you had
a decent meal?

6
00:01:05.191 --> 00:01:07.359
Come on.

7
00:01:07.443 --> 00:01:09.570
Mary's always happy
to have you at the table.

8
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:12.865
- Nothing you say is gonna change my mind.
- Damn it. Reggie.

9
00:01:12.948 --> 00:01:16.869
You're the most talented
superhero I've ever seen.

10
00:01:16.952 --> 00:01:19.538
Yet you're... you're throwing it all away

11
00:01:19.622 --> 00:01:21.582
slinging yayo for gangbangers?

12
00:01:21.665 --> 00:01:23.709
You don't know me. Coach.
You don't know nothin'.

13
00:01:23.793 --> 00:01:26.295
I know you've got heart.

14
00:01:26.378 --> 00:01:28.005
I know you want more than this.

15
00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:29.423
You've got a choice. son.

16
00:01:29.507 --> 00:01:32.384
Either outrun this life.

17
00:01:32.468 --> 00:01:35.304
or you can run yourself
into an early grave.

18
00:01:35.387 --> 00:01:38.724
Now. please. It's me. Coach Brink.

19
00:01:38.808 --> 00:01:41.477
Come back with me.

20
00:01:41.560 --> 00:01:43.562
To the suburbs.

21
00:01:45.481 --> 00:01:47.483
Yeah. what I want doesn't matter.

22
00:01:48.734 --> 00:01:50.778
I'll never be free of these streets.

23
00:01:50.861 --> 00:01:53.030
Cut! Holy fuck.

24
00:01:53.113 --> 00:01:55.241
Holy fuck. we're not gonna beat that.

25
00:01:55.324 --> 00:01:57.868
That was fucking perfect.
We're going again.

26
00:01:57.952 --> 00:02:00.329
- I don't...
- Ferrell fucking Streep.

27
00:02:00.412 --> 00:02:02.331
There are tears.

28
00:02:02.414 --> 00:02:04.124
Literal tears.

29
00:02:04.208 --> 00:02:06.210
Who's happy they spent two weekends

30
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:07.962
at the Compton Youth Center now. huh?

31
00:02:08.045 --> 00:02:10.214
I'm not giving off too much
of a <i>Blind Side</i> vibe. am I?

32
00:02:10.297 --> 00:02:12.550
As if that's a bad thing?

33
00:02:12.633 --> 00:02:13.777
Are you... Wait. what is that smell?

34
00:02:13.801 --> 00:02:15.511
Will everyone stop?

35
00:02:15.594 --> 00:02:17.179
What is that smell?!

36
00:02:17.263 --> 00:02:19.473
Is it... Is that you?

37
00:02:19.557 --> 00:02:20.975
I had falafel for lunch.

38
00:02:21.058 --> 00:02:22.643
What?

39
00:02:22.726 --> 00:02:25.312
I smell an Oscar nomination.

40
00:02:25.396 --> 00:02:26.647
Shut up. man.

41
00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.400
- No. I won't.
- Don't jinx it.

42
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:30.860
You can't jinx gold. Look at me.

43
00:02:30.943 --> 00:02:33.988
You better make some shelf space.
De Niro. Do you hear me?

44
00:02:34.071 --> 00:02:35.781
All right. let's get you back to one. huh?

45
00:02:35.865 --> 00:02:37.175
- I'm gonna watch playbacks. okay?
- Absolutely.

46
00:02:37.199 --> 00:02:39.910
Yeah. let's get him some cans. please?
Thank you.

47
00:02:39.994 --> 00:02:41.704
One more quick thing.

48
00:02:41.787 --> 00:02:43.067
Let's sidebar here a little bit.

49
00:02:43.122 --> 00:02:44.766
It feels like you're having
a little bit of trouble

50
00:02:44.790 --> 00:02:46.292
getting out of the starters' block.

51
00:02:47.293 --> 00:02:49.003
Maybe it's the scene.

52
00:02:49.086 --> 00:02:50.480
Baby. this scene sings.
All right. look at me.

53
00:02:50.504 --> 00:02:54.133
In the arc of your character.
this is your low point. right?

54
00:02:54.216 --> 00:02:56.343
Everybody's given up on you.
you're all alone.

55
00:02:56.427 --> 00:02:57.469
until the coach...

56
00:02:57.553 --> 00:03:00.097
Swoops in and saves me from the ghetto?

57
00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:01.408
No. no. no. you actually save each other.

58
00:03:01.432 --> 00:03:03.225
It's a very balanced narrative.

59
00:03:03.309 --> 00:03:06.812
All the sensitivity readers
that we hired. they all agreed.

60
00:03:06.896 --> 00:03:08.939
- My brother was the only coach I ever had.
- Right.

61
00:03:09.023 --> 00:03:11.025
He was a waiter at Buster Beaver.

62
00:03:11.108 --> 00:03:12.610
not a fucking crack dealer.

63
00:03:13.736 --> 00:03:15.738
And he must be so proud of you right now.

64
00:03:15.821 --> 00:03:18.824
Let's get this train back on the tracks.

65
00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:22.161
- Just give me a minute.
- Yeah. sure.

66
00:03:23.245 --> 00:03:25.539
Wait. wait. you know what?
One more tiny little thing.

67
00:03:25.623 --> 00:03:29.293
You said what I want "doesn't matter."

68
00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:30.753
But as scripted. it's actually

69
00:03:30.836 --> 00:03:33.923
what I want "don't matter." okay?

70
00:03:34.006 --> 00:03:35.007
All right. good stuff.

71
00:03:35.090 --> 00:03:37.301
All right. everybody.
let's get back to one!

72
00:03:37.384 --> 00:03:39.261
I want to make this fucking day!

73
00:03:42.348 --> 00:03:44.224
Hey. can we talk?

74
00:03:44.308 --> 00:03:46.602
You don't talk. It's like your one thing.

75
00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:48.371
Look. playing Noir has been
a meaningful challenge.

76
00:03:48.395 --> 00:03:49.623
but yesterday was wack as fuck.

77
00:03:49.647 --> 00:03:52.816
I've never actually
murdered anyone before.

78
00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:54.711
Does Homelander make us
kill people. like. a lot?

79
00:03:54.735 --> 00:03:57.196
And when does. do we just... do it?

80
00:03:58.614 --> 00:04:00.741
Look. don't get me wrong.
I am stoked to be here

81
00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:04.078
and I am down to ride the wave.
I'm just having trouble

82
00:04:04.161 --> 00:04:05.430
with Noir's motivation. you feel me?

83
00:04:05.454 --> 00:04:08.248
His motivation is being
a braindead maniac.

84
00:04:08.332 --> 00:04:10.042
Just keep your mouth shut

85
00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:11.835
and do as you're fucking told.

86
00:04:14.838 --> 00:04:17.198
<i>Violence
in our blood-splattered streets</i>

87
00:04:17.257 --> 00:04:19.510
<i>against decent. hardworking Americans.</i>

88
00:04:19.593 --> 00:04:21.321
<i>Folks. if you're thinking
of letting your children</i>

89
00:04:21.345 --> 00:04:23.597
<i>play carefree outside
and without supervision.</i>

90
00:04:23.681 --> 00:04:24.890
<i>think again.</i>

91
00:04:24.974 --> 00:04:26.600
<i>I mean. these two animals.</i>

92
00:04:26.684 --> 00:04:28.394
<i>Benny Long and Ian Rashford.</i>

93
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:30.270
<i>savagely beat three good men to death</i>

94
00:04:30.354 --> 00:04:32.022
<i>outside the courthouse yesterday.</i>

95
00:04:32.106 --> 00:04:34.125
{\an8}<i>The Starlighters have shown
their true colors. folks.</i>

96
00:04:34.149 --> 00:04:38.404
{\an8}<i>rioting at multiple quote-unquote
"peaceful demonstrations"</i>

97
00:04:38.487 --> 00:04:39.989
{\an8} <i>across the country.</i>

98
00:04:40.072 --> 00:04:42.241
<i>I. for one. do not take our liberties</i>

99
00:04:42.324 --> 00:04:43.677
<i>in this great country for granted.</i>

100
00:04:43.701 --> 00:04:46.078
<i>But apparently the Starlighters
feel differently.</i>

101
00:04:46.161 --> 00:04:49.081
Let's see. Soy for pH.

102
00:04:49.164 --> 00:04:51.500
hyaluronic acid for deep moisturizing

103
00:04:51.583 --> 00:04:54.128
- and arginine for circulation.
- What is all that?

104
00:04:54.211 --> 00:04:56.046
Um. I'm a Voughtality consultant.

105
00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:58.382
5K away from
the red. white and blue Caddy.

106
00:04:58.465 --> 00:04:59.967
I thought it might be helpful.

107
00:05:00.050 --> 00:05:03.053
You... You work for Vought?

108
00:05:03.137 --> 00:05:05.055
Voughtality. "For a Super You."

109
00:05:05.139 --> 00:05:08.559
You know Vought killed
my girlfriend. right?

110
00:05:08.642 --> 00:05:11.270
I'm literally fighting them right now.

111
00:05:12.688 --> 00:05:15.232
I think I have rosemary oil.

112
00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.942
it's really good for the joints.

113
00:05:17.026 --> 00:05:19.278
Can you just...
Can you stop please? Just for...

114
00:05:19.361 --> 00:05:22.740
- Please stop. Mom. stop. Just stop.
- Okay. I'm sor...

115
00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:25.534
Okay. sorry. sorry. Just. um...

116
00:05:27.161 --> 00:05:28.412
I'm sorry.

117
00:05:29.788 --> 00:05:31.373
You look good.

118
00:05:31.457 --> 00:05:32.916
Got tall.

119
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.477
Yeah. that adds up. since
the last time you saw me

120
00:05:34.501 --> 00:05:35.919
I was six fucking years old!

121
00:05:36.003 --> 00:05:37.713
Please don't yell at me.

122
00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:40.090
- What are you doing here?
- The hospital called.

123
00:05:40.174 --> 00:05:41.842
Yeah. when they couldn't reach me.

124
00:05:41.925 --> 00:05:43.969
And I'm here now. so...

125
00:05:44.053 --> 00:05:46.597
He doesn't need you. Neither of us do.

126
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.974
Your dad didn't tell you.

127
00:05:49.058 --> 00:05:50.225
Shit.

128
00:05:51.477 --> 00:05:52.853
About what?

129
00:05:52.936 --> 00:05:57.524
He gave me power of attorney.
including medical decisions.

130
00:05:57.608 --> 00:05:59.526
And he signed a DNR.

131
00:05:59.610 --> 00:06:01.695
H-He didn't update his will?

132
00:06:01.779 --> 00:06:03.238
He did.

133
00:06:04.698 --> 00:06:08.410
Why the fuck would he give you
power of attorney over me?

134
00:06:08.494 --> 00:06:11.622
Well. I mean. we've been talking.

135
00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:14.291
the last year or two. now and then.

136
00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:16.710
Besides that. you'd have to ask him.

137
00:06:16.794 --> 00:06:17.878
But Hughie. don't worry.

138
00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:19.671
- I am really good in a crisis.
- Don't.

139
00:06:19.755 --> 00:06:22.633
And I-I-I can handle this.

140
00:06:22.716 --> 00:06:24.259
I promise.

141
00:06:27.137 --> 00:06:28.639
You promise.

142
00:06:30.432 --> 00:06:31.767
Hughie...

143
00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:33.227
Wait.

144
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:50.452
You leave the money on the dresser?

145
00:06:55.207 --> 00:06:57.126
I didn't want to wake you up.

146
00:06:58.752 --> 00:07:00.045
Hey.

147
00:07:02.381 --> 00:07:04.800
Yeah. maybe you should
stay in bed today. no?

148
00:07:04.883 --> 00:07:06.552
Yeah...

149
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.347
Could've been a lot worse.

150
00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:13.392
I mean. it would've been
a lot worse if you weren't there.

151
00:07:18.397 --> 00:07:19.481
Thank you.

152
00:07:24.444 --> 00:07:26.655
Oh.

153
00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:28.824
Starlight.

154
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:31.451
Work.

155
00:07:42.963 --> 00:07:44.548
Your speech therapist Gloria

156
00:07:44.631 --> 00:07:46.276
has filled me in on the work
you've been doing.

157
00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:47.634
How's that been going?

158
00:07:57.561 --> 00:08:00.856
You know. psychological mutism

159
00:08:00.939 --> 00:08:04.318
is often a symptom of trauma
in one's past.

160
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:05.777
What do you think about that?

161
00:08:12.034 --> 00:08:13.243
I couldn't agree more.

162
00:08:13.327 --> 00:08:15.162
But sometimes you have
to confront your past

163
00:08:15.245 --> 00:08:16.830
in order to be free of it.

164
00:08:18.874 --> 00:08:19.875
Okay.

165
00:08:19.958 --> 00:08:21.710
Why don't we start with something simple?

166
00:08:21.793 --> 00:08:25.464
Tell me about your parents.

167
00:08:32.095 --> 00:08:33.639
<i>Jesus.</i>

168
00:08:33.722 --> 00:08:34.973
You're just telling us now?

169
00:08:35.057 --> 00:08:37.809
Have you seen any specialists.
have you. um...

170
00:08:37.893 --> 00:08:39.102
So how long you got?

171
00:08:39.186 --> 00:08:41.313
It's none of your fucking business.

172
00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:42.832
- I'm not sure why I'm telling you at all.
- What's going on?

173
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:45.234
Let's just say I got
an angel on my shoulder.

174
00:08:45.317 --> 00:08:47.194
And she's a right bloody nag.

175
00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:49.905
Butcher. I tried to warn you
that that shit was poison.

176
00:08:49.988 --> 00:08:51.406
You ain't one of us.

177
00:08:51.490 --> 00:08:53.408
- Hey!
- All right!

178
00:08:55.160 --> 00:08:56.453
A word.

179
00:09:08.298 --> 00:09:09.591
You're done.

180
00:09:09.675 --> 00:09:10.926
- What?
- Fired.

181
00:09:11.009 --> 00:09:12.636
Grab your shit and get the fuck out.

182
00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:14.680
I level with you lot
and this is the thanks I get.

183
00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:16.181
Fuck me.

184
00:09:16.265 --> 00:09:18.100
- See what being honest gets you?
- Honest?

185
00:09:18.183 --> 00:09:20.623
Motherfucker. you've been lying to us
for the last six months.

186
00:09:20.686 --> 00:09:22.104
Not telling ain't lying.

187
00:09:22.187 --> 00:09:24.564
Look. you need all the help
you can get. mate.

188
00:09:24.648 --> 00:09:27.192
Not from you. You're a liability. Butcher.

189
00:09:27.276 --> 00:09:30.070
I ain't gonna let this stand. then.

190
00:09:30.153 --> 00:09:31.780
The Boys is mine.

191
00:09:31.863 --> 00:09:34.032
Says a dying man with one last bluff.

192
00:09:36.326 --> 00:09:39.579
Now grab your shit and get the fuck out.

193
00:09:39.663 --> 00:09:41.206
Or I'll throw you out.

194
00:09:43.917 --> 00:09:45.961
- Just...
- I don't want to hear it.

195
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:48.130
He's out.

196
00:09:48.213 --> 00:09:50.632
You can join him if you don't like it.

197
00:09:57.389 --> 00:10:01.310
Small-town kid grows up on
a Montana ranch with his mom.

198
00:10:01.393 --> 00:10:05.564
On the surface. he's an everyday
all-American boy.

199
00:10:05.647 --> 00:10:08.233
But deep in his heart. he knows
he's different. special.

200
00:10:08.317 --> 00:10:10.027
He's always asking himself. "Who am I?"

201
00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:11.695
Then one day that question is answered

202
00:10:11.778 --> 00:10:14.406
when Homelander flies down from the sky

203
00:10:14.489 --> 00:10:16.408
and says with tears in his eyes...

204
00:10:16.491 --> 00:10:17.659
No tears.

205
00:10:17.743 --> 00:10:20.454
...and says. proudly.
"Son. it's time for you

206
00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.122
to take your place by my side."

207
00:10:22.205 --> 00:10:24.708
And for Ryan it feels surprising.
yet inevitable.

208
00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:28.378
He always knew he
was destined for greatness.

209
00:10:28.462 --> 00:10:30.547
Because he came from greatness.

210
00:10:31.882 --> 00:10:33.342
- Oh.
- Wow.

211
00:10:33.425 --> 00:10:36.553
Oh. buddy. can you believe that?

212
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:38.555
W-What do you think?

213
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:42.142
It's cool. I guess.

214
00:10:43.226 --> 00:10:44.394
You guess?

215
00:10:44.478 --> 00:10:47.105
I think it looks amazing.

216
00:10:47.189 --> 00:10:50.776
- Oh. so amazing. Really marketable.
- So marketable.

217
00:10:50.859 --> 00:10:53.028
The whole pitch blows.

218
00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:55.822
It... does not blow.

219
00:10:55.906 --> 00:10:58.575
It blows. harder than Nancy Reagan
on the MGM backlot.

220
00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:00.786
I'm sorry. why are you here?

221
00:11:00.869 --> 00:11:03.288
Vought got rid of most of the sidekicks
after Gunpowder.

222
00:11:03.372 --> 00:11:04.599
The settlements exceeded profitability.

223
00:11:04.623 --> 00:11:05.767
Yeah. but I don't think Ryan

224
00:11:05.791 --> 00:11:09.044
is gonna file an HR complaint
against me.

225
00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:11.505
A what?

226
00:11:11.588 --> 00:11:13.590
Ryan is the first natural-born superhero.

227
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:14.901
And his brand needs to reflect that.

228
00:11:14.925 --> 00:11:17.636
He's not one of Vought's lab rat freaks.

229
00:11:17.719 --> 00:11:21.139
He was chosen... by fate. God. whatever...

230
00:11:21.223 --> 00:11:23.058
to be the one who saves the world.

231
00:11:23.141 --> 00:11:24.309
Yes.

232
00:11:24.393 --> 00:11:26.436
But let's not forget

233
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:28.146
why he is special.

234
00:11:28.230 --> 00:11:29.398
Shall we?

235
00:11:29.481 --> 00:11:30.857
He's my son.

236
00:11:30.941 --> 00:11:34.444
Chosen by God. sure. but. uh...

237
00:11:34.528 --> 00:11:36.238
made by me.

238
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:39.616
The chosen one narrative
only works if he stands alone.

239
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:42.828
Harry Potter. Neo. Luke Skywalker.

240
00:11:42.911 --> 00:11:44.621
Hollywood's trained people to fall in love

241
00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:46.331
with white boy lone saviors.

242
00:11:46.415 --> 00:11:49.751
So. America will want
to fall in love with Ryan.

243
00:11:52.671 --> 00:11:53.755
What is this?

244
00:11:53.839 --> 00:11:55.090
Uh. it's a crime itinerary.

245
00:11:55.173 --> 00:11:57.634
Your first save. Congratulations. son.

246
00:11:57.717 --> 00:11:59.428
I'm not on the call sheet.

247
00:11:59.511 --> 00:12:02.556
You wanted a kingdom for your son.

248
00:12:02.639 --> 00:12:06.143
I'm helping you get it.

249
00:12:12.023 --> 00:12:13.150
- Excellent.
- Mm.

250
00:12:13.233 --> 00:12:14.609
Just as we discussed.

251
00:12:14.693 --> 00:12:17.154
Feel free to move forward.

252
00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:19.239
Thanks.

253
00:12:19.322 --> 00:12:21.408
Ah. if you don't mind?

254
00:12:21.491 --> 00:12:23.368
Hmm.

255
00:12:23.452 --> 00:12:26.455
I'm here because Homelander wants me here.

256
00:12:26.538 --> 00:12:28.081
Because he trusts me.

257
00:12:57.944 --> 00:12:59.237
